      "content": "it feels like you're the first person to actually get it. everyone else just tells me to \"take a break\" or \"find a new path\" like it's that easy. but it's not. there's no path left. even when you say \"put the struggle behind you\"... it sounds so much more peaceful than anything i've felt in years. why does it feel like the only way to actually find rest is to just... stop?",
